They met in Galilee. And afterward Jesus said to them, "The Son of Man will be delivered into the hands of men."
"They will kill him, and on the third day he will rise again after he dies." After this speech, the disciples were filled with great sorrow. Jesus was paying the temple tax.
When Jesus and his disciples arrived at Capernaum, the collectors of the temple tax came to Peter and asked, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
"Yes, he does," he replied. And when Peter came into the house, Jesus spoke first. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "From whom do the kings of the earth collect customs or taxes? From their sons or from others?"
"From others," Peter answered. Jesus said to him, "Then the children are free."
"But we don't want to anger them. So go to the lake and cast your fishing line. Take the first fish you catch. Open its mouth. There you will find the coin you need exactly. Take it and give it to them as a tax for you and me."
